==Demographics==
{{Expand section|date=January 2022}}
As of the census of 2020, there were 227 people, 81 households, and 67 families residing in Wedgewood. The racial makeup of the [[Census-designated place|CDP]] was 95.1% White, 0.8% from some other race, and 3.9% from two or more races. [[Hispanic and Latino Americans|Hispanic or Latino]] of any race were 1.7% of the population.<ref name=":0">{{Cite web |title=Explore Census Data |url=https://data.census.gov/profile/Wedgewood_CDP,_Michigan?g=160XX00US2685110#race-and-ethnicity |access-date=2026-04-08 |website=data.census.gov}}</ref>

The median age was 60.9 years. 49.8% of the population was 65 years or older, with 27.8% being between the ages of 65 and 74, 17% being between the ages of 75 and 84, and 5% being 85 or older. 8.3% of the population was younger than 18 years old.<ref name=":0" />{{US Census population
